##
## Commands
##
@node commands "Easy Quake Commands"


 @{b}Easy Quake Commands@{ub}


        @{b}GAME Command@{ub}

 Sets a Easy Quake game extention or pack.
      
 This gadget opens up a file requester which lets you choose the game's directory
 or extention directory.



        @{b}ADDPARM Command@{ub}

 Supply extra parameters for usage in Quake.
 
        eg. +scr_conspeed 3000;name "Helios"
            r_drawviewmodel 0
      

        @{b}SAFE Command@{ub}

 Runs Quake with no network options and with minimum memory.
      

 
        @{b}NOSOUND Command@{ub}
    
 Disables any sound.
 

 
        @{b}MMUHACK Command@{ub}
    
 Runs program with MMU hack in place.
 

        
        @{b}CDDEVICEALIKE Command@{ub}
    
 The CD is cd.device alike.
         


        @{b}CDAUDIO Command@{ub}
    
 Turns on CD Audio, after you do this make sure to set the CDDEVICE and
 CDUNIT parameters.
 

 
        @{b}CDDEVICE Command@{ub}
    
 When CDAUDIO is on, enter the device driver for your CD.
  


        @{b}CDUNIT Command@{ub}
    
 When CDAUDIO is on, enter the device unit for your CD.


 
        @{b}CROSSHAIR Command@{ub}
    
 Enable/disable targetting crosshair.



        @{b}WATERWARP Command@{ub}
    
 Enable/disable waterwarp (underwater distortion).



        @{b}MODELOFF Command@{ub}
    
 Enable/disable model of weapon (speed up for some users).

 
 
        @{b}MINMEMORY Command@{ub}
    
 Use as little memory as possible, if it is selected the MEMORY gadget will
 become unavailable.
            


        @{b}MEMORY Command@{ub}
    
 Use <nn> MB of memory, if it is greater than 0 the MINMEMORY gadget will
 become unavailable. If the MEMORY setting is equal to 0, the command
 is not issued to Quake (cause Quake needs some... all or a part of it).
 The max. available memory is detected automatically.



        @{b}NETWORK Command@{ub}
 
 Sets network options. Either disabled or enabled, to disable a protocol
 use NOTCPIP, NOSERIAL or NOIPX. Do not forget to set port, when network
 is enabled the port is added.
 

 
        @{b}PORT Command@{ub}
 
 The network port to use.               



        @{b}LISTEN Command@{ub}
 
 Make it a listen server, this way you can still play while others are
 connected to you. When this command is not selected, your machine will
 act as a dedicated server.   
     

     
        @{b}FPU Command@{ub}
 
 Change Floating Point mode.               

                  
@endnode

